    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 8,000 RPM redline. The powertrain is mated to a traditional 6-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing M-Variable limited-slip differential. Mechanically sorted, the vehicle has undergone essential preventative maintenance including a comprehensive VANOS system refresh and rod bearing replacement. The chassis is reinforced at the rear subframe mounting points to ensure structural rigidity. Handling is sharp thanks to a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup, retaining the iconic balance and tactile steering feedback this platform is known for. The exterior presents well with minor age-appropriate patina, while the interior remains a functional, enthusiast-oriented cockpit.",
